@abstract:
Declared future intent for the contractiles system.
Tracks security improvements, operational maturity, tooling adoption,
and observability goals for the policy gateway.
@end

@requires:
- section: Trust-Engine
- section: Control-Plane
- section: Pipeline
- section: Introspection
- section: Tooling
- section: Deprecations
@end

## Trust-Engine

### hardware-key-management
- description: Integrate hardware-backed key management (TPM 2.0, YubiKey)
- status: declared
- priority: high
- target: 2026-Q3
- evidence: config/tpm.toml exists
- notes: Waiting on TPM firmware support for Dilithium5

### node-attestation
- description: Support node attestation for deployment targets
- status: declared
- priority: medium
- target: 2026-Q4
- evidence: command: attestation-agent --version
- depends_on: hardware-key-management

## Control-Plane

### gitops-config-promotion
- description: Move to GitOps-backed configuration promotion
- status: accepted
- priority: high
- target: 2026-Q2
- evidence: .flux/ exists
- notes: Evaluating Flux vs ArgoCD for policy promotion

### canary-rollouts
- description: Add canary and staged rollout support
- status: declared
- priority: medium
- evidence: config/canary.ncl exists

## Pipeline

### nickel-policy-language
- description: Adopt Nickel as the primary policy language
- status: in-progress
- priority: high
- evidence: policy/policy.ncl exists
- notes: Migration from YAML to Nickel underway; policy.ncl already exists

### signed-artifact-promotion
- description: Automate policy promotion from dev to prod with signed artifacts
- status: declared
- priority: medium
- depends_on: hardware-key-management
- evidence: trust: artifact-signature

### contractile-cli-integration
- description: Integrate contractile CLI into CI/CD pipeline
- status: realised
- priority: critical
- evidence: command: contractile --version
- notes: Realised 2026-03-14 — Rust CLI built, installed, symlinks in ~/.local/bin

## Introspection

### decision-latency-metrics
- description: Expose decision latency and policy evaluation metrics
- status: declared
- priority: low
- evidence: command: curl -s localhost:9090/metrics | grep -q decision_latency

### request-tracing
- description: Add end-to-end tracing for request decisions
- status: declared
- priority: low
- evidence: config/tracing.toml exists

## Tooling

### just-integration
- description: Generate contractile.just and import into Justfile
- status: realised
- priority: high
- evidence: contractile.just exists
- notes: Realised 2026-03-14 — contractile.just generated (35 recipes), imported in Justfile

### k9-validation-contracts
- description: Write Yard-level K9 components to validate A2ML files
- status: realised
- priority: medium
- evidence: contractiles/k9/validators/ exists
- notes: Realised 2026-03-14 — 4 Yard-level validators (must/trust/dust/intent)

### symlink-installation
- description: Install must/trust/dust/intend/k9 symlinks to ~/.local/bin/
- status: realised
- priority: high
- evidence: command: which must
- notes: Realised 2026-03-14 — 6 symlinks installed (must/trust/dust/intend/k9/contractile)

## Deprecations

### legacy-yaml-contractiles
- description: Phase out legacy YAML-format contractile files (Mustfile, Dustfile, Intentfile)
- status: realised
- priority: medium
- evidence: command: find contractiles/ -name 'Mustfile' -o -name 'Dustfile' -o -name 'Intentfile' | grep -v '.a2ml' | wc -l | grep -q '^0$'
- notes: Removed all YAML/Haskell legacy files across contractiles, proven, explicit-trust-plane

### ada-must-runner
- description: Replace Ada must runner with unified Rust contractile CLI
- status: realised
- priority: medium
- evidence: command: contractile must --help
- notes: Realised 2026-03-14 — Rust CLI supersedes Ada runner; Ada preserved as reference
